Calling all Hip Do-Gooders - Dance for Health!
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Join DJs Tim, Adam Baker, and Alex Blackstock for an evening at Little Baobob and support community health initiatives in Nicaragua. Yes that's right, our friends are hip do-gooders and you can be too. $10 at the door for all the booty shaking beats you can handle, from 10 pm - 2 am. All proceeds benefiting Teach For Health's education programs in Nicaragua, which provide training and materials for community health workers in the San Ramon municipality.

Next Monday, we will be diving into Chapter 5: Recursive Structures and Processes. We will explore recursion in a variety of contexts, moving towards settling on a definition for ourselves. I've decided to postpone a week to give myself and others time to really wrap their heads around this section– so if you've been missing out, now's the time to catch up! Plan to meet up at 7 to mingle and order take-out, discussion will begin at 7:30.
